'''公众科学（Citizen Science）'''，'''公民科学'''或'''群智科学'''，是指"[[公众参与|公众参与]]的科学研究", 包括非职业的[[科学家|科学家]]、[[科学爱好者|科学爱好者]]和志愿者参与的科研活动, 范围涵盖科学问题探索、新技术发展、数据收集与分析等。从形式上看，公众科学已被定义为“系统地收集和分析数据；开发技术；对自然现象的测试，以及这些活动的散发由主要基于业余爱好的研究者。”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.openscientist.org/2011/09/finalizing-definition-of-citizen.html |title=Finalizing a Definition of "Citizen Science" and "Citizen Scientists" |publisher=OpenScientist |date=2011-09-03 |accessdate=2012-10-11 |archive-date=2020-09-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200920113145/http://www.openscientist.org/2011/09/finalizing-definition-of-citizen.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>其成果通常是通过提高科学界的能力，以及增加公众对科学的理解来推动科学研究的进步。

著名的公民科学家包括[[艾萨克·牛顿|艾萨克·牛顿]]、[[弗洛伦斯·南丁格尔|弗洛伦斯·南丁格尔]]、[[本杰明·富兰克林|本杰明·富兰克林]]和[[查尔斯·达尔文|查尔斯·达尔文]]<ref name=BF&TF>{{Cite journal|last=Fecko|first=Kristin Meece|title=The relevance of Benjamin Franklin's and Thomas Jefferson's Technical Writing for Modern Communicators|journal=Electronic Theses and Dissertations|url=https://stars.library.ucf.edu/etd/4741|date=August 2014|access-date=2021-11-12|archive-date=2021-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211101041252/https://stars.library.ucf.edu/etd/4741/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。 在《[[新科學人|新科學人]]》杂志和提高[[酸雨|酸雨]]意识的运动中可以找到"公众科学(CS)"一词的首次使用。公众科学发现的一个例子是1781年[[威廉·赫歇爾|威廉·赫歇爾]]首次观测到的[[天王星|天王星]]<ref name=R.H_1>{{cite book |last=Holmes |first=Richard |date=2008 |title=The Age of Wonder |publisher=Vintage Books |location=New York |isbn=978-1-4000-3187-0}}</ref>。

公众科学项目一般由公众和科学家合作发起。<ref name=biodiversity-science2013>{{cite journal|author=张健|coauthors=陈圣宾, 陈彬, 杜彦君, 黄晓磊, 潘绪斌, 张强|title=http://www.biodiversity-science.net/CN/abstract/abstract9808.shtml|journal=生物多样性|year=2013|volume=21|issue=6|pages=738-749|url=http://www.biodiversity-science.net/CN/abstract/abstract9808.shtml|accessdate=2013-12-20|archive-date=2019-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726070744/http://www.biodiversity-science.net/CN/abstract/abstract9808.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref> 公众科学有时也包含在诸如“公众参与科学研究”和{{le|参与行动研究|Participatory action research}}。<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.nature.com/doifinder/10.1038/466685a|pages=685–687|title=Citizen science: People power|journal=Nature|volume=466|issue=7307|language=en|date=2010-08-04|accessdate=2018-04-02|doi=10.1038/466685a|author=Eric Hand}}</ref>

== 伦理 ==
已经被发表了各种研究，探讨了公众科学的[[伦理学|伦理]]，包括[[知识产权|知识产权]]和项目设计等问题。（例如<ref name=Re&Po/><ref name=Resnik_2015>{{cite journal|title=A framework for addressing ethical issues in citizen science|author1=D. B. Resnik|author2=K. C. Elliot|author3=A. K. Miller|journal=Environmental Science & Policy|volume=54|pages=475–481|date=December 2015|doi=10.1016/j.envsci.2015.05.008}}</ref><ref name=Bowser_2015>{{cite journal|title=Privacy in Participatory Research: Advancing Policy to support Human Computation|author1=A. E. Bowser|author2=A. Wiggins|journal=Human Computation|date=2015|pages=19–44|doi=10.1534/hc.v2i1.3}}</ref><ref name=Hoffman_2014>{{cite journal|title=Citizen Science: The Law and Ethics of Public Access to Medical Big Data|author=S. Hoffman|journal=Berkeley Technology Law Journal|date=September 2014|volume=Case Legal Studies Research Paper No. 2014-21}}</ref><ref name=Scassa_2015>{{cite web|title=Managing Intellectual Property Rights in Citizen Science: A Guide for Researchers and Citizen Scientists|author1=T. Scassa|author2=Chung H.|url=https://www.wilsoncenter.org/sites/default/files/managing_intellectual_property_rights_citizen_science_scassa_chung.pdf|publisher=Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars|date=2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705153453/https://www.wilsoncenter.org/sites/default/files/managing_intellectual_property_rights_citizen_science_scassa_chung.pdf|archivedate=2017-07-05|df=|access-date=2018-08-13}}</ref>）公民科学协会（CSA），总部设在[[康乃爾鳥類學實驗室|康乃爾鳥類學實驗室]]和欧洲公民科学协会（ECSA），总部设在[[柏林自然博物馆|柏林自然博物馆]]，设有道德和原则工作组<ref name=CSA_1>{{cite web|title=CSA Working Group on Ethics|url=http://citizenscience.org/association/about/working-groups/ethics-working-group/|publisher=Citizen Science Association|accessdate=24 August 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170825062443/http://citizenscience.org/association/about/working-groups/ethics-working-group/|archivedate=2017-08-25|df=}}</ref><ref name=ECSA_2>{{cite web|title=ECSA Principles & Standards in Citizen Science: Sharing Best Practice & Building Capacity|url=http://www.ecsa.citizen-science.net/taxonomy/term/205|publisher=ECSA|accessdate=18 August 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818072003/http://ecsa.citizen-science.net/taxonomy/term/205|archivedate=2016-08-18|df=}}</ref>。

== 历史 ==
“公众科学”是一个相当新的名词，但它是一个旧的做法。在20世纪之前，科学往往是[[绅士科学家|绅士科学家]]，业余或自费研究人员的追求，如[[艾萨克·牛顿|艾萨克·牛顿]]爵士，[[本杰明·富兰克林|本杰明·富兰克林]]和[[查尔斯·达尔文|查尔斯·达尔文]]等等。然而，到20世纪中叶，科学被大学和政府研究实验室雇用的研究人员主导。 到了1970年代，这种转变受到了质疑。 哲学家[[保罗·费耶阿本德|保罗·费耶阿本德]](Paul Feyerabend)呼吁“科学民主化”<ref>{{cite book |author=Paul Feyerabend |author-link=Paul Feyerabend |title=Science in a free society |publisher=[[New_Left_Books|New Left Books]]|location=London |year=1982 |pages= |isbn=0-86091-753-3 |oclc= |doi= |accessdate=}}</ref>。 生物化学家[[埃爾文·查戈夫|埃爾文·查戈夫]]（Erwin Chargaff）主张在[[笛卡尔|笛卡尔]]，[[牛顿|牛顿]]，[[莱布尼兹|莱布尼兹]]，[[布丰|布丰]]，和[[达尔文|达尔文]]科学中以自然爱好的业余爱好者回归科学；主导科学的应该是“业余爱好而非金钱偏见的技术官僚”<ref>{{cite book |author=Erwin Chargaff |author-link=Erwin Chargaff |title=Heraclitean fire: sketches from a life before nature |publisher=[[Rockefeller_University_Press|Rockefeller University Press]] |location=New York |year=1978 |pages= |isbn=0-87470-029-9 |oclc= |doi= |accessdate=}}</ref>。

2016年的一项研究表明，公众科学的最大影响是生物学，保护和生态学研究，主要用作收集和分类数据的方法<ref name=kullberg>{{cite journal|author1=C. Kullenberg |author2=D. Kasperowski |title=What Is Citizen Science? – A Scientometric Meta-Analysis|journal=PLoS ONE|date=14 January 2016|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0147152|volume=11|pages=e0147152|pmid=26766577|pmc=4713078|bibcode=2016PLoSO..1147152K}}</ref>。

=== 業餘天文學 ===
{{main|業餘天文學|星系動物園}}
[[File:Telescope_trailer_22.jpg|right]]和聚會，例如[[Stellafane|Stellafane]]。]]

長久以來，[[天文學|天文學]]的領域充滿了[[業餘天文學|業餘天文學家]]，一直到今天仍然一樣<ref>{{cite journal |last=Mims III |first=Forrest M. |authorlink=Forrest Mims |title=Amateur Science—Strong Tradition, Bright Future |journal=Science |year=1999 |volume=284 |issue=5411 |pages=55–56 |doi=10.1126/science.284.5411.55 |quote=Astronomy has traditionally been among the most fertile fields for serious amateurs [...] |bibcode = 1999Sci...284...55M }}</ref>。

整體而言，業餘天文學家觀察各種天體和現象，有時也[[業餘望遠鏡製造|建造自己的設備]]。業餘天文學家的目標通常包括月球、行星、恆星、彗星、流星雨和各種各樣的[[深空天體|深空天體]]，像是星團、星系、和星雲。彗星和恆星的觀測還用於衡量當地的[[霞光|人造輝光]]<ref name="GaN">{{cite journal|last=Kyba|first=Christopher C. M.|author2=Wagner, Janna M. |author3=Kuechly, Helga U. |author4=Walker, Constance E. |author5=Elvidge, Christopher D. |author6=Falchi, Fabio |author7=Ruhtz, Thomas |author8=Fischer, Jürgen |author9= Hölker, Franz  |title=Citizen Science Provides Valuable Data for Monitoring Global Night Sky Luminance|journal=[[Scientific_Reports|Scientific Reports]]|volume=3|doi=10.1038/srep01835|bibcode = 2013NatSR...3E1835K |date=2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Sciezor | first1 = T. | doi = 10.1093/mnras/stt1297 | title = A new astronomical method for determining the brightness of the night sky and its application to study long-term changes in the level of light pollution | journal = Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society | volume = 435 | pages = 303–310 | year = 2013 | pmid =  | pmc = |bibcode = 2013MNRAS.435..303S }}</ref>。業餘天文學的一個分支，業餘[[天文攝影|天文攝影]]，涉及到夜空的拍照。許多愛好這專注於特定的天體、天體的類型、或事件的類型，進行他們感興趣的觀測<ref>{{cite web| url= http://www.amsmeteors.org/| title= The Americal Meteor Society| accessdate= 24 August 2006| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20060822135040/http://www.amsmeteors.org/| archivedate= 2006年8月22日| deadurl= no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Jerry|last=Lodriguss|url=http://www.astropix.com/|title=Catching the Light: Astrophotography|accessdate=24 August 2006|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060901185541/http://www.astropix.com/|archivedate=2006年9月1日|deadurl=no}}</ref>。

[[美國變星觀測者協會|美國變星觀測者協會]]自1911年以來，蒐集變星的資料，進行教育和專業分析，並鼓勵其成員參與[[#公眾科學|公眾天文]]和其它的網站<ref>http://www.citizensky.org/ {{Wayback|url=http://www.citizensky.org/ |date=20161201190005 }} Citizen Sky</ref>。

=== 鸟类学 ===
{{main|观鸟}}
公众科学项目越来越注重为科学研究提供益处<ref>Bonney, R. and LaBranche, M. (2004). Citizen Science: Involving the Public in Research. ASTC Dimensions. May/June 2004, p. 13.</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Baretto | first1 = C. | last2 = Fastovsky | first2 = D. | last3 = Sheehan | first3 = P. | year = 2003 | title = A Model for Integrating the Public into Scientific Research | url = | journal = [[Journal_of_Geoscience_Education|Journal of Geoscience Education]] | volume = 50 | issue = 1| pages = 71–75 }}</ref><ref>McCaffrey, R.E. (2005). Using Citizen Science in Urban Bird Studies. Urban Habitats. 3 (1). p. 70-86.</ref>。{{le|北美鸟类物候学计划|North American Bird Phenology Program}}（历史上称为鸟类迁徙和分布记录）可能是公众在美国收集鸟类信息的最早集体努力<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwrc.usgs.gov/bpp/|title=North American Phenology Program|publisher=|accessdate=30 July 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160729190651/http://www.pwrc.usgs.gov/bpp/|archivedate=2016-07-29|df=}}</ref>。 该计划的历史可以追溯到1883年，由韦尔斯·伍德布里奇·库克(Wells Woodbridge Cooke)发起。 库克在北美范围建立了一个观察员网络，以收集鸟类迁徙记录。 [[奥杜邦学会|奥杜邦学会]]（The National Audubon Society）的[[圣诞节鸟类统计|圣诞节鸟类统计]]（Christmas Bird Count；缩写CBC）始于1900年，是公众科学长期存在的另一个例子，一直持续到今天。 公众科学家帮助收集将由专业研究人员分析的数据，并可用于产生鸟类种群和生物多样性指标。

=== 地震学 ===
自1975年以来，为了改善地震探测和收集有用信息，{{le|欧洲-地中海地震中心|European-Mediterranean Seismological Centre}}监测地震目击者对其网站的访问，并依赖Facebook和Twitter<ref name=EMSC>{{cite web| title=EMSC History| url=https://www.emsc-csem.org/about| publisher=The European-Mediterranean Seismological Centre| access-date=16 January 2018| deadurl=no| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170908143401/https://www.emsc-csem.org/about/| archivedate=2017-09-08| df=}}</ref>。

=== 水文学 ===
公众科学已被用于提供[[水文学|水文学]]（流域科学）的宝贵数据，特别是洪水风险，[[水质|水质]]和[[水管理|水资源管理]]<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Starkey|first1=Eleanor|last2=Parkin|first2=Geoff|last3=Birkinshaw|first3=Steve|last4=Large|first4=Andy|last5=Quinn|first5=Paul|last6=Gibson|first6=Ceri|title=Demonstrating the value of community-based (‘citizen science’) observations for catchment modelling and characterisation|journal=Journal of Hydrology|date=2017|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0022169417301646|doi=10.1016/j.jhydrol.2017.03.019|bibcode=2017JHyd..548..801S|access-date=2018-08-18|archive-date=2021-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210525161440/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0022169417301646|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Community Involvement in UK Catchment Management|url=http://www.fwr.org/Catchment/frr0021.pdf|publisher=Foundation for Water Research|accessdate=27 April 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170428053522/http://www.fwr.org/Catchment/frr0021.pdf|archivedate=2017-04-28|df=}}</ref>。 互联网使用和智能手机的拥有的增长使用户能够使用收集和分享实时洪水风险信息，例如利用社交媒体和基于网络的表格。

=== 淡水鱼类 ===
水族馆爱好者及其各自的组织对鱼类保护充满热情，并且通常比科学研究人员更了解特定的鱼类物种和群体<ref>{{Cite web|last=Page|first=Michael Le|title=Home aquarium hobbyists are helping save 30 rare fish from extinction|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/2218831-home-aquarium-hobbyists-are-helping-save-30-rare-fish-from-extinction/|access-date=2020-09-30|website=New Scientist|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031232103/https://www.newscientist.com/article/2218831-home-aquarium-hobbyists-are-helping-save-30-rare-fish-from-extinction/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他们通过发现新物种、维护包含数千种物种（例如[[鲶鱼|鲶鱼]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=PlanetCatfish • home of aquarium catfishes|url=https://www.planetcatfish.com/|access-date=2020-09-30|website=www.planetcatfish.com|language=en-gb|archive-date=2021-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210330042013/https://www.planetcatfish.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、 墨西哥淡水鱼<ref>{{Cite web|title=Main Index {{!}} Freshwater Fishes of Mexico|url=https://mexfish.info/|access-date=2020-09-30|website=mexfish.info|archive-date=2020-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200918094552/https://mexfish.info/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、 鳉鱼<ref>{{Cite web|last=Dr Jean H. HUBER|title=Huber's Killi-Data online - All available information on Killifish|url=http://www.killi-data.org|access-date=2020-09-30|website=www.killi-data.org|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211044410/http://www.killi-data.org/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、 慈鲷 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Main Index {{!}} Cichlid Room Companion|url=https://cichlidae.com/|access-date=2020-09-30|website=cichlidae.com|archive-date=2020-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924195119/https://cichlidae.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref> ）生态信息的广泛数据库，在淡水鱼类保护中发挥了重要作用，并成功地为保护项目保留和提供濒危和野外灭绝的物种<ref>{{Cite web|title=The hidden ark: How a grassroots initiative can help save fish from extinction|url=https://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2019-10/au-tha093019.php|access-date=2020-09-30|website=EurekAlert!|language=en|archive-date=2019-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001214347/https://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2019-10/au-tha093019.php|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Maceda-Veiga|first1=Alberto|last2=Domínguez-Domínguez|first2=Omar|last3=Escribano-Alacid|first3=Josep|last4=Lyons|first4=John|date=2014-09-08|title=The aquarium hobby: can sinners become saints in freshwater fish conservation?|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/faf.12097|journal=Fish and Fisheries|volume=17|issue=3|pages=860–874|doi=10.1111/faf.12097|issn=1467-2960|access-date=2021-11-12|archive-date=2021-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210330041954/https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/faf.12097|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 农业 ===
农民参与实验在[[农业科学|农业科学]]中有着悠久的传统<ref>{{cite journal |last1= Gosset|first1= William S.|date=1936 |title= Co-Operation in Large-Scale Experiments|journal= Supplement to the Journal of the Royal Statistical Society|volume= 3|issue= 2|pages=115–136|doi= 10.2307/2983667|jstor= 2983667}}</ref>。 公民参与粮食系统不同部分的机会很多<ref>{{cite journal |last1= Ryan|first1= S.F|last2= Adamson|first2= N.L.|last3=Aktipis|first3=A.|last4=Andersen|first4=L.K.|last5=Austin|first5=R.|last6= Barnes|first6=L.|last7=Beasley|first7=M.R.|last8=Bedell|first8=K.D.|last9= Briggs|first9= S.|last10= Chapman|first10= B.|date=2018 |title= The role of citizen science in addressing grand challenges in food and agriculture research|journal= Proceedings of the Royal Society B|volume= 285|issue= 1891|pages= 20181977|doi= 10.1098/rspb.2018.1977|pmid= 30464064|pmc= 6253361}}</ref>。公民科学被积极用于气候适应的作物品种选择，涉及数千名农民<ref>{{cite journal |last1= van Etten|first1= Jacob|last2= de Sousa|first2= Kauê|last3=Aguilar|first3=Amílcar |last4=Barrios|first4=Mirna |last5=Coto|first5=Allan |last6= Dell'Acqua|first6=Matteo |last7=Fadda|first7=Carlo |last8=Gebrehawaryat|first8=Yosef |last9= van de Gevel|first9= Jeske |last10=Gupta |first10=Arnab|last11=Kiros|first11=Afewerki Y. |last12=Madriz|first12=Brandon |last13=Mathur|first13=Prem |last14=Mengistu|first14=Dejene K.|last15=Mercado|first15=Leida |last16=Nurhisen Mohammed|first16=Jemal |last17=Paliwal|first17=Ambica |last18=Pè|first18=Mario Enrico |last19=Quirós|first19=Carlos F. |last20=Rosas|first20=Juan Carlos |last21=Sharma|first21=Neeraj |last22=Singh|first22=S.S.|last23=Solanki|first23=Iswhar S.| last24=Steinke|first24=Jonathan |date=2019 |title= Crop variety management for climate adaptation supported by citizen science|journal= Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America|volume= 285|issue= 1891|pages= 4194–4199|doi= 10.1073/pnas.1813720116|pmid= 30782795|pmc= 6410884|doi-access= free}}</ref>。

